<div class="vf-section-header">
  <h2 class="vf-section-header__heading vf-section-header__heading--is-link" id="section-link-text">
    <a href="/web-optimisation-framework/about/what-is-lro/">What is LRO?</a>
    <svg aria-hidden="true" class="vf-section-header__icon | vf-icon vf-icon-arrow--inline-end" width="1em" height="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
      <path d="M0 12c0 6.627 5.373 12 12 12s12-5.373 12-12S18.627 0 12 0C5.376.008.008 5.376 0 12zm13.707-5.209l4.5 4.5a1 1 0 010 1.414l-4.5 4.5a1 1 0 01-1.414-1.414l2.366-2.367a.25.25 0 00-.177-.424H6a1 1 0 010-2h8.482a.25.25 0 00.177-.427l-2.366-2.368a1 1 0 011.414-1.414z" fill="" fill-rule="nonzero"></path>
    </svg>
  </h2>
  <p class="vf-section-header__text">A set of guidelines for designing, developing, and maintaining web services optimised for low-resource environments, covering performance, adaptive design, accessibility, offline support, and content efficiency.</p>
</div>
<div class="vf-section-header">
  <h2 class="vf-section-header__heading" id="section-text">Why it matters?</h2>
  <p class="vf-section-header__text">An unoptimised site becomes inaccessible for users in low-bandwidth, environments. The LRO framework provides a structured way to measure, fix, and validate web performance through a scored benchmark system, audit guidance, and optimisation strategies.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="vf-section-header | vf-u-padding__top--800">
<h2 class="vf-section-header__heading">Explore key LRO topics</h2>
</div>
